[{"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Apple denied unionized workers better benefits, NLRB claims", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An illustration of the Apple logo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/kFZmdBkxB8VbvnZa44cSZExk1Vo=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72893878/STK071_ACastro_apple_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"8sqLlh\">The National Labor Relations Board (NLRB) claims Apple denied a set of new benefits to unionized employees at its Towson, Maryland store, <a href=\"https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/24174155-apple-nlrb-unfair-labor-practice?responsive=1&amp;title=1\">according to a complaint filed on Tuesday</a>.</p>\n<p id=\"OaONtf\">In the complaint, the NLRB alleges Apple didn\u2019t extend enhanced benefits to Towson workers with the goal of \u201cdiscouraging\u201d other employees from unionizing. Some of those new benefits include new healthcare options, a free Coursera subscription, and prepaid tuition at some colleges.</p>\n<p id=\"H6C1kC\">The Apple store in Towson became the <a href=\"ht", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972688/apple-union-unfair-labor-practice-towson-nlrb", "date_published": "2023-11-22T22:14:57+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best smart locks you can buy right now", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Door locks on a bright yellow, pink and orange graphic\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/5dO8UhrbXIz1LtBQXXPtGHMXh8c=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/71491011/226294_Doorbell_buying_Guide_Kradtke.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration: The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Never get locked out again with a smart lock you can control from your phone, with your voice, or with just a touch of your finger.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23393163/best-smart-door-lock\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23393163/best-smart-door-lock", "date_published": "2023-11-22T21:45:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "A look inside both the Legion Go and Steam Deck OLED", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture showing the Legion Go and the Steam Deck OLED with their back covers removed.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/3kn86RGwFS2yHvjZWcjk1TC1Pa8=/0x48:2000x1381/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72893607/SteamDeckOLEDlegiongo.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Legion Go (top) and the Steam Deck OLED (bottom), disassembled.</em> | Images: iFixit</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"OtOBzH\">iFixit <a href=\"https://go.redirectingat.com?id=66960X1514734&amp;xs=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifixit.com%2FNews%2F86954%2Fhandheld-head-to-head-steam-deck-oled-v-legion-go&amp;referrer=theverge.com&amp;sref=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theverge.com%2F2023%2F11%2F22%2F23972676%2Fsteam-deck-oled-legion-go-teardown-ifixit-repairability-hall-effects-sticks\" rel=\"sponsored nofollow noopener\" target=\"_blank\">published</a> a dual teardown of <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23951655/steam-deck-oled-review\">Valve\u2019s Steam Deck OLED</a> and the Lenovo Legion Go ", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972676/steam-deck-oled-legion-go-teardown-ifixit-repairability-hall-effects-sticks", "date_published": "2023-11-22T21:08:51+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best gaming deals for Black Friday 2023", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A close-up of a white DualSense controller resting against a PlayStation 5 console.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/pDnPcY3wRNsQnoSMqIgo_45cOkU=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72893119/vpavic_4261_20201023_0028.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Vjeran Pavic / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"SLvuFB\">There\u2019s no better time to stock up on games and gaming accessories than <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23939216/black-friday-guide-cyber-monday-tech-gadgets-2023\">Black Friday</a>, and this year, we\u2019re seeing sizable discounts on some of the biggest titles released this year \u2014 a year, need I remind you, that\u2019s been inundated with many excellent games.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><div id=\"csoMnq\"><div></div></div></div>\n<p id=\"pbjdk6\">While not all of this year\u2019s biggest games are getting significant discounts, titles like <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0BPMTJJ6D?tag=theverge02-20\" r", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23971228/black-friday-2023-gaming-game-deals-cyber-monday", "date_published": "2023-11-22T19:30:37+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Bard can now watch YouTube videos for you", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A graphic showing Bard\u2019s logo with Gmail, Drive, Docs, and other apps\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/F_HVrPCg69HxznMUIQRHq7h_1kQ=/129x0:1071x628/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72893066/google_bard_extensions.0.png\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Bard continues to tap into Google\u2019s constellation of services and platforms in increasingly useful ways.</em> | Image: Google</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"bbWSMZ\">Bard, Google\u2019s AI chatbot, has <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/9/19/23878999/google-bard-ai-chatbot-gmail-docs-drive-extensions\">steadily been getting more useful</a> after <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/3/21/23650472/google-bard-ai-chatbot-hands-on-test\">a lackluster introduction</a>. Now, <a href=\"https://www.androidauthority.com/google-bard-youtube-understanding-3388018/\">as noted by <em>Android Authority,</em></a> the bot\u2019s YouTube integration <a href=\"https://bard.google.com/updates\">is getting a handy upgr", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972636/bard-youtube-extension-update-search-video-content", "date_published": "2023-11-22T19:18:40+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Ford shrinks its EV battery factory plans in Michigan", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Ford logo on the front of an F-150 Lightning\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/lkF78tk2ouw4ezDZzMUrDKzJPsA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892990/ahawkins_220504_5202_0010.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Closeup of an all-electric F-150 Lightning.</em> | Photo by Andrew Hawkins / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"czzFLD\">Ford announced it is cutting production capacity on its upcoming electric vehicle battery plant, amid cooling customer demand for purchasing EVs and rising labor costs. The <a href=\"https://media.ford.com/content/fordmedia/fna/us/en/news/2023/11/21/blue-oval-battery-park-michigan-update.html\">automaker says</a> it will reduce its original $3.5 billion planned investments to build the Michigan plant to somewhere around $2 billion and is now only expecting to hire 1,700 workers instead of 2,500.</p>\n<p id=\"F39rAq\">Ford had <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/2/11/23595909/ford-battery-p", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972680/ford-michigan-ev-battery-plant-reduction-plans", "date_published": "2023-11-22T19:01:33+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best Black Friday deals under $100", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A hand holding up the Kindle Paperwhite\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/VRNp93gtsOhpHG4GX23T2Lf60DQ=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892831/cgartenberg_211020_4803_0003.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Kindle Paperwhite is a popular gift that\u2019s going for less than $100 when you buy the nearly identical kid-friendly model.</em> | Photo by Chaim Gartenberg / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"Xpmerm\">It\u2019s the most wonderful time of the year? Pfft, more like the most expensive. Gifts, travel, decorations, parties, delicious meals\u2026 these all add up and can put a real dent in your wallet. That\u2019s why we\u2019re working hard to help you save in every way, from <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23951136/gifts-under-100-best-cheap-tech-ideas-2023-budget\">curating budget-friendly gift guides</a> to <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/21587765/black-friday-cyber-monday-best-deals-how-to-find\">offering deal-hunting tips", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23965961/black-friday-2023-tech-deals-under-100-cyber-monday", "date_published": "2023-11-22T18:32:30+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The WiiM Amp is a stream-everything receiver with Mac Mini vibes", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A picture of the WiiM Amplifier from a three-quarter angle. It\u2019s gray, shaped roughly like a Mac Mini, with a large knob on the right front that has a play button in the middle. Left of that, a dark gray pencil-thick line extends almost to the left corner. Above the left end of the line there\u2019s a purple-colored power LED, and above it on the right, six circular LEDs appear to indicate volume \u2014 the left four are lit up, with the rightmost of those slightly dimmed. The other two are dark.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/yVVW1Nt7qaPgSnDh6XOC1fBOiio=/160x0:1890x1153/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892652/WiiM_Amp___Lifestyle_4.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The $299 WiiM Amp has outputs for passive stereo speakers and plenty of streaming support.</em> | Image: Linkplay Technology</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wTvSp7\">Linkplay Technology announced a new addition to its lineup today: the <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0CGC", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972352/wiim-amp-airplay-2-chromecast-wireless-receiver-vintage-hi-fi", "date_published": "2023-11-22T17:47:52+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Read Microsoft\u2019s internal memo about the chaos at OpenAI", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"OpenAI - Microsoft\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/x5mAdEgf1QxEMWyb5xGIPQqlhWk=/2x0:3724x2481/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892648/1795954328.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo by Berke Bayur/Anadolu via Getty Images</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"iQAX2J\">In the early hours of Wednesday morning, OpenAI announced that <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23967223/sam-altman-returns-ceo-open-ai\">Sam Altman is returning as CEO</a>, following a <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/17/23965982/openai-ceo-sam-altman-fired\">shock firing</a> on Friday. Over the weekend, it looked like Altman and OpenAI co-founder Greg Brockman <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/20/23968829/microsoft-hires-sam-altman-greg-brockman-employees-openai\">might end up at Microsoft</a>, leading a new AI research lab. But after days of negotiation, that\u2019s no longer the case and OpenAI has appointed a new board of directors and brought ba", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972572/microsoft-internal-memo-kevin-scott-openai", "date_published": "2023-11-22T17:46:27+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Hayao Miyazaki is very convincing", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A still image from the Studio Ghibli film The Boy and the Heron.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/g1U5le2dbrpv2bVgC13h-GUzunA=/182x0:1739x1038/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892346/HERON_img_7.5.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>The Boy and the Heron.</em> | Image: GKIDS</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Longtime Evangelion animator Takeshi Honda had already signed up to work on another film when The Boy and the Heron director came calling. \u201cWhen Miyazaki says that to you, really there\u2019s no way to say no,\u201d Honda says.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23971512/boy-and-the-heron-takeshi-honda-interview-evangelion\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23971512/boy-and-the-heron-takeshi-honda-interview-evangelion", "date_published": "2023-11-22T17:00:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Kodak\u2019s new Super 8 film camera is actually coming out", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Kodak\u2019s new Super 8 camera.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/gRLCTtxWbsjnG82y1BnSqf6iwig=/1x0:1324x882/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892252/Super_8_Detailed_Render_Black.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Kodak\u2019s new Super 8 camera.</em> | Image: Kodak</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"xCXWrr\">Kodak is gearing up to actually sell the Super 8 film camera it announced way back at CES 2016. It\u2019s updated the <a href=\"https://www.kodak.com/en/motion/page/super-8-camera?CID=go&amp;idhbx=super8camera&amp;ref=404media.co\">camera\u2019s product page</a> with a new \u201csign up to buy\u201d button to allow potential customers to register their interest. Kodak\u2019s global managing director for motion picture, Vanessa Bendetti, tells <em>The Verge </em>that the company expects the camera to go on sale in limited quantities in the US on December 4th, before releasing in Canada, the UK, and other European markets. </p>\n<p id=\"0Uq7SX\">When it goes on sale, the", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972513/kodak-super-8-film-camera-lcd-screen-price-release-date-specs-features", "date_published": "2023-11-22T16:41:18+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Squid Game: The Challenge is a morbid LARP trapped inside a reality TV show", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"A group of people wearing green track suits and white T-shirts. Over the photo is a transparent overlay to create the impression that the pictured people are being watched from a distance.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/x2r0ikfu5vwdmKDhD5yUT_JeeE4=/282x0:3318x2024/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72892218/Squid_Game__The_Challenge_n_S1_E1_00_07_19_11R.0.jpeg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Participants in Netflix\u2019s </em>Squid Game: The Challenge<em>.</em> | Image: Netflix</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>The most dystopian thing about Netflix\u2019s new Squid Game reality show is how much fun its contestants seem to be having.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23971416/squid-game-the-challenge-review-netflix\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23971416/squid-game-the-challenge-review-netflix", "date_published": "2023-11-22T16:30:00+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The best doorbell cameras", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/sxSidjIZg78EqJRBlKmHTpPiwcA=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/70564714/VRG_ILLO_5012_K_Radtke_Doorbell_Buying_Guide.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Illustration by Kristen Radtke / The Verge, Shutterstock</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>We pick the best video doorbell cameras for keeping an eye on people, packages, and anything else that comes across your front porch. </p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/22954554/best-video-doorbell-camera\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/22954554/best-video-doorbell-camera", "date_published": "2023-11-22T16:10:10+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Eminem is coming to Fortnite\u2019s The Big Bang event", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"An image showing Eminem in Fortnite\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/Yz_E7keOF55IBIk1nvLWOwQL2Nk=/150x0:1770x1080/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72891983/eminem_fortnite.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Image: Epic Games</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"2rcepR\">The <a href=\"https://www.dexerto.com/fortnite/eminem-fortnite-live-event-and-skin-leaked-for-chapter-4-finale-2393291/\">leaks</a> were true: Eminem is coming to <em>Fortnite</em> as part of the game\u2019s Chapter 4 finale. <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/Cz89v4zM7-a/?igshid=N2ViNmM2MDRjNw%3D%3D\">Epic Games has confirmed</a> Eminem will appear during the live finale, while players will get to purchase a few different skins modeled after the rapper.</p>\n<p id=\"A7Eaoj\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/21/23970772/fortnite-big-bang-live-event-date\"><em>Fortnite</em>\u2019s finale event, called The Big Bang</a>, kicks off on December 2nd at 2PM ET. In an <a href=\"https://www.", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972384/eminem-fortnite-og-chapter-4-finale", "date_published": "2023-11-22T15:42:15+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "Niantic sexual bias lawsuit can proceed after judge blocks arbitration effort", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Somebody playing Pok\u00e9mon Go and trying to catch Mewtwo.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/cCvhavqa_fbKH9hl84b3FLA-HNI=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72891924/DSCF5354.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption><em>Niantic attempted to avoid the sexual bias lawsuit going to trial.</em> | Photo by Sam Byford / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n  <p id=\"wR3Yp1\">A California judge ruled that a class-action sexual bias lawsuit against Niantic could proceed, blocking the <em>Pok\u00e9mon Go</em> creator\u2019s attempt to move the suit into arbitration.</p>\n<p id=\"jzbYgD\">Los Angeles County Superior Court Judge Elihu Berle found that allegations raised by two female former employees regarding exposure to a hostile gender-based work environment were protected under the 2021 Ending Forced Arbitration Act.</p>\n<div class=\"c-float-left c-float-hang\"><aside id=\"VgVZof\"><q>Attorney Genie Harrison described the outcome as a \u201cwatershed moment for sexual", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/2023/11/22/23972339/niantic-sexual-discrimination-lawsuit-gender-bias-arbitration", "date_published": "2023-11-22T15:27:21+00:00", "permanent": false, "bookmarked": false, "dead": false, "artist": "The Verge", "album": "The Verge", "user": null, "language": "en-US", "thumbnail": null, "age": null, "page_rating_contents": 0, "page_rating_votes": 0, "page_rating_visits": 0, "page_rating": 0, "tags": [], "comments": [], "vote": 0}, {"source": "https://www.theverge.com/rss/index.xml", "title": "The Verge\u2019s favorite holiday gifts under $25", "description": "<figure>\n      <img alt=\"Photo illustration of hands holding various products on a brightly colored background of stars.\" src=\"https://cdn.vox-cdn.com/thumbor/1H0sEX0F0mODlwoLCW8drLTlf8M=/0x0:2040x1360/1310x873/cdn.vox-cdn.com/uploads/chorus_image/image/72891806/236830_UNDER_25_Gift_Guide_Artboards_CVirginia_LEDE_2040x1360.0.jpg\" />\n        <figcaption>Photo Illustration by Amelia Holowaty Krales and Cath Virginia / The Verge</figcaption>\n    </figure>\n\n\n  \t\t <p>Whether you need a stocking stuffer or a white elephant present, we\u2019ve got an inexpensive gift idea for nearly every occasion.</p>\n  <p>\n    <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/23874403/tech-gifts-under-25-best-cheap-ideas-stocking-stuffers-2023-budget\">Continue reading&hellip;</a>\n  </p>", "link": "https://www.theverge.com/23874403/tech-gifts-under-25-best-cheap-ideas-stocking-stuffers-2023-budget", "date_publi